I"ª	<h2 id="background">Background</h2>
<p>Completed his PhD in Biomedical Engineering at New Jersey Institute of Technology (NJIT), Newark, NJ, USA in 2005 and holds a BSc in Applied Physics and an MSc in Biomedical Engineering, also from NJIT. He joined the Department of Neurology at Columbia University Medical Center, NYC, NY, USA for eight years for a post-doctoral fellowship and continued as faculty. After spending two years as a research scientist at the PERFORM Center at Concordia University, Montreal, Quebec, Canada he joined the University of Ottawa, Ontario, Canada in 2016.</p>

<h2 id="research-interests">Research Interests</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Healthy cognitive aging</li>
  <li>Cognitive reserve</li>
  <li>Brain-behavior relationships</li>
  <li>Neuroimaging</li>
  <li>Moderated-mediation statistical analyses</li>
  <li>Mathematical modeling</li>
  <li>Distributed computing</li>
  <li>Olfaction</li>
  <li>Open science</li>
</ul>

